article.headline: N. Dakota St. 68, Oral Roberts 55
article.story: FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- North Dakota State jumped out to a 7-0 lead and never trailed Saturday as it concluded its season with a 68-55 win over Summit League-leading Oral Roberts. NDSU (16-13, 10-8) is not eligible for the Summit League tournament until next season. Ben Woodside had two of NDSU's seven 3-pointers and 19 points to lead all scorers. He also had six assists. Brett Winkelman had a double-double with 18 points and 12 rebounds. He was perfect on six free throws and the Bison outscored the Golden Eagles 15-5 from the line. Baskets by Lucas Moormann, Ben Woodside and Winkelman staked the Bison to a 7-0 lead five minutes into the game. Oral Roberts tied it 13-13 with 8:59 left on a Shawn King basket, but the Eagles never had a lead after NDSU ran off 10 straight points. The Bison led 29-19 at the half. Oral Roberts (21-8, 16-2) shot 38 percent.The Golden Eagles have clinched the conference title. Adam Liberty was Oral Roberts' only double-figure scorer with 12 points.
